Logistic regression takes as input 0 or 1 as a response variable y, along with the covariate(s) x, and estimates the prob. of success (Y=1) for each value of x. Correct Ans: 1, 2 and 3 only. The operator `-` removes the specified terms. It can also be use to remove the intercept term, i.e. when fittign a linear model `y ~ x - 1` specifies a line through the origin. A model with no #RStats #DataScience [TimeStamp:06112021220005]
